EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to Medicaid; requiring an application to participate in Medicaid
as a provider to be [notarized;] accompanied with a verification of
the identity and signature of the applicant; establishing the means
by which the identity and signature of an applicant may be
established; and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires an application to participate in Medicaid as a provider to contain a
2 statement that all matters stated within the application are true and accurate. Existing law
3 requires a natural person who is the applicant, or is authorized to act on behalf of the
4 applicant, to sign the [application] statement under the pains and penalties of perjury.
5 Existing law provides that a person who signs such [an application] a statement knowing that
6 the application contains information which is false, whether in whole or in part, and whether
7 by commission or omission, is guilty of a category D felony. (NRS 422.550) This bill
8 additionally requires that an application submitted [by a person] to participate in Medicaid as
9 a provider be [notarized, in addition to being signed under the pains and penalties of perjury
10 and containing the required statement that all matters stated within the application are true and
11 accurate.] accompanied by verification of the identity and signature of the person who
12 signed the statement. This bill specifies that a person may verify his or her identity and
13 signature for this purpose by: (1) oath or affirmation before a notary public or other
14 person authorized by law to administer oaths or affirmations; or (2) through the use of
15 an electronic identity verification system.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 422.550 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 422.550 1. Each application or report submitted to participate as a provider,
3 each report stating income or expense upon which rates of payment are or may be
4 based, and each invoice for payment for goods or services provided to a recipient
5 must contain a statement that all matters stated therein are true and accurate, signed

